                                                    </span>
                                                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                                                    <p style="font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                        class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">The
                                                            ‘Embracing Tolerance’ Programme is aimed at 11 – 18 year
                                                            olds and is designed to address Key Stages 3-4
                                                        </span><em><span
                                                                style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">diversity</span></em><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">,
                                                            and </span><em><span
                                                                style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">personal
                                                                wellbeing </span></em><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">aspects
                                                            of the PHSE/Citizenship programme, and works in harmony with
                                                            the </span><em><span
                                                                style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">SEAL
                                                            </span></em><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">initiative
                                                            within the National Curriculum. Furthermore, the programme
                                                            enables schools to meet crucial Ofsted inspection criteria,
                                                            such as </span><em><span
                                                                style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">‘Community
                                                                Cohesion Duty’,</span></em><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">
                                                            enhancing ‘</span><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">pupils’
                                                            spiritual, moral, social and cultural development’
                                                        </span><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">and
                                                        </span><em><span
                                                                style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">‘Judgement
                                                                on Leadership and Management’ </span></em><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">in
                                                            the way the school </span><em><span
                                                                style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">‘promotes
                                                                equal opportunity and</span></em><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">
                                                        </span><em><span
                                                                style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">tackles
                                                                discrimination.’ </span></em><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">This
                                                            provides an academic context for TIUK to encourage pupils to
                                                            explore attitudes and values and to develop knowledge,
                                                            skills and understanding that support inclusion, challenge
                                                            racism and extremism, and promote diversity. The objective
                                                            is to bring together communities from different races and
                                                            faiths and&nbsp;encourage a shared sense of
                                                            belonging.</span></p>
                                                    <p>&nbsp;</p><strong><span
                                                            style="font-size: 12pt; color: #72a476; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Social
                                                            Exclusion</span></strong><span
                                                        style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">
                                                        <font color="#000000"><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">&nbsp;
                                                            </span></font>
                                                    </span><span
                                                        style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'"></span><span
                                                        style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">
                                                        <font color="#000000"><span
                                                                style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS'">
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Our
                                                                        programme aims to address problems of social
                                                                        exclusion, which can lead to increasing levels
                                                                        of intolerance, discrimination, bullying, and
                                                                        violent crimes including knifings and gun crime
                                                                        in our schools and on our streets. The main
                                                                        objective of the programme is to improve
                                                                        community relations, promote cohesion and offer
                                                                        a positive alternative to violence. The overall
                                                                        aim is to strengthen and consolidate a shared
                                                                        sense of belonging and community cohesion by
                                                                        bringing together youth from different races,
                                                                        cultures, socio-cultural backgrounds and diverse
                                                                        persuasions. We will achieve this by supporting
                                                                        the youth in changing their attitudes and
                                                                        values, addressing issues of social intolerance
                                                                        and religious extremism, and promoting respect
                                                                        for the diversity of cultures, ethnic groups and
                                                                        nationalities. Social exclusion can also occur
                                                                        when young people feel alienated and polarised
                                                                        due to ethnic and /or religious tensions. These
                                                                        vulnerable young people need a rational
                                                                        counterbalance to help them withstand the
                                                                        influence of extremist groups, who actively
                                                                        recruit disenfranchised young people to support
                                                                        their cause.</span></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><strong><span
                                                                            style="font-size: 12pt; color: #72a476; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Methodology</span></strong>
                                                                </p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Under
                                                                        the leadership of the Programme Coordinator, a
                                                                        team of volunteers specialising in multicultural
                                                                        and multidisciplinary techniques, will work in
                                                                        close partnership with appropriately religious,
                                                                        educational and community-based agencies. We
                                                                        welcome sensitive partnerships with the
                                                                        police.</span></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">The
                                                                        programme is delivered through workshops. Using
                                                                        scenarios presenting discriminatory behaviour as
                                                                        initial stimuli, staff will act as facilitators,
                                                                        guiding the students through focused activities,
                                                                        allowing for exploration of prejudice,
                                                                        discrimination and tolerance, and their results
                                                                        on individuals. Diversity will be explored and
                                                                        the audience will be given the opportunity to
                                                                        analyse good practice.</span></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><strong><span
                                                                            style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">The
                                                                            learning objectives of the vocational
                                                                            educational </span></strong><strong><span
                                                                            style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">programme
                                                                            "</span></strong><strong><em><span
                                                                                style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Embracing
                                                                                Tolerance</span></em></strong><strong><span
                                                                            style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">":</span></strong>
                                                                </p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span>·<strong>Understanding
                                                                            inequalitie</strong></span><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'"><strong>s</strong></span>
                                                                </p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">·</span><strong><span
                                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Respecting
                                                                            diversities</span></strong></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">·</span><strong><span
                                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Understanding
                                                                            different c</span></strong><strong><span
                                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">ommunities</span></strong>
                                                                </p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">·</span><strong><span
                                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Developing
                                                                            knowledge of various
                                                                        </span></strong><strong><span
                                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">faiths</span></strong>
                                                                </p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">·</span><strong><span
                                                                            style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Learning
                                                                            to be tolerant</span></strong></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><strong><span
                                                                            style="color: #72a476; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Areas
                                                                            of potential conflict should be examined
                                                                            with a view to offering viable and tolerant
                                                                            alternatives. Staff will provide information
                                                                            regarding the cultures of
                                                                            others.</span></strong></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><strong><span
                                                                            style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">(1)Case-study
                                                                            led discussion</span></strong></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">·<span>&nbsp;
                                                                        </span></span><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Examining
                                                                        an incident of intolerance or discrimination
                                                                        (for example, of a person or group because of
                                                                        their religious beliefs).</span></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">·<span>&nbsp;
                                                                        </span></span><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Imagining
                                                                        in some detail what might be involved for all
                                                                        the participants (perpetrator, bystander and
                                                                        <span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>victim).</span>
                                                                </p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">·<span>&nbsp;
                                                                        </span></span><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Encouraging
                                                                        participation through the discussion of personal
                                                                        experience,</span></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">·<span>&nbsp;
                                                                        </span></span><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Neutrality
                                                                        will be maintained throughout the session,
                                                                        avoiding any moral comment with the aim of
                                                                        understanding the views and opinions of the
                                                                        participants.</span></p>
                                                                <p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span
                                                                            style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">(2)
                                                                            Examination of images.</span></strong></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">•
                                                                        Observing images of a variety of people; some
                                                                        represented in the public eye, others unknown to
                                                                        the public.</span></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">•
                                                                        Brainstorming of associations with that image,
                                                                        to examine prejudices and stimulate discussion
                                                                        amongst participants.</span></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">•
                                                                        Discussion of different outcomes, including how
                                                                        stereotypical attitudes portrayed by the media
                                                                        and other sources can influence personal
                                                                        judgements.</span></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><strong><span
                                                                            style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">(3)
                                                                            Cross-over role-play.</span></strong></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">•
                                                                        Participants asked to present a situation where
                                                                        some form of intolerance or discrimination can
                                                                        be portrayed (ranging from simple neighbourly or
                                                                        school based disputes to issues concerning
                                                                        racial or religious intolerance or
                                                                        discrimination).</span></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">•
                                                                        Participants asked to take on the roles of those
                                                                        involved, by producing dialogue and acting out
                                                                        scenes, </span><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">with
                                                                        the goal of finding a positive outcome to
                                                                        overcome discrimination.</span></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">•
                                                                        Done in a cross-over way, so that participants
                                                                        play a non-familiar role. Here moralising,
                                                                        natural comment would be allowed, especially
                                                                        those taken from the perspective of a
                                                                        non-familiar role (i.e., white/non-white,
                                                                        Muslim/Christian, male/female, etc.)</span></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><strong><span
                                                                            style="color: #72a476; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">W</span></strong><span
                                                                        style="color: #72a476; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">orkshops
                                                                        will last over 1 – 3 sessions depending upon the
                                                                        audience. We are working towards having our
                                                                        workshops accredited for vocational and
                                                                        educational purposes; as such we seek to have
                                                                        the programme accredited as a Vocationally
                                                                        Recognised Qualification with a view to
                                                                        extending the wider benefits. In association
                                                                        with local schools we are applying our programme
                                                                        to the principles of ASDAN and Citizenship, as
                                                                        required by curriculum standards. We are already
                                                                        working in schools in the London boroughs of
                                                                        Hackney, Tower Hamlets, Enfield and Merton. Our
                                                                        staff will also take on additional service user
                                                                        support roles such as advocacy and sign-posting
                                                                        to other appropriate support agencies where
                                                                        specific needs are identified.</span></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: #72a476; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">&nbsp;</span><strong><span
                                                                            style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">Monitoring
                                                                            and Evaluation</span></strong></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">There
                                                                        will be regular monitoring and evaluation of the
                                                                        programme. Participatory monitoring and
                                                                        evaluation with the beneficiaries will be used
                                                                        to adjust the programme to be more in line with
                                                                        the expectations of the target audience. The
                                                                        programme outcomes will be measured by
                                                                        monitoring:</span></p>
                                                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                    class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: 'Trebuchet MS','sans-serif'">·<span>&nbsp;
